  "texts": [
    "Additionally, the authors evaluated benchmark by using Bidirectional LSTM, fastText embeddings, and sentence transformer models.",
    "The improved NR/IndicbnBERT model stood out among these others with a Macro-F1 of 86%.",
    "Goyal et al. [97] studied to create unique word embeddings, or \"boosted word embeddings,\" which are capable of easily picking up contextual information\" where boosted word embeddings are the result of combining word length, part of speech, and character-based convolutional embeddings.",
    "They achieved f-score values of 73.99%, 66.94%, and 77.95%, respectively by using enhanced word embeddings, named entity recognition systems for Hindi, Punjabi, and bilingual Hindi and Punjabi.",
    "Ghosh et al. [50] proposed ACLM (Attention-map aware keyword selection for Conditional Language Model fine-tuning which is a unique data augmentation for challenging NER with limited resources."
